Condoms with chili powder, firecrackers support Tanzania&#39;s protection of elephants
Conservationists in Tanzania use an unorthodox way to discourage elephants from entering human settlements - throwing condoms filled with chili powder at them.
The method has proven effective and the Honeyguide Foundation, which came up with the idea years ago, has partnered with US Conservation to step up its support by training volunteers in villages in northern Tanzania, a four-step non-violent method of protecting their homes and wildlife Harvest to use without harming animals.
Previously, many used spears to defend themselves.
