The federal government will cut funding by 30 percent from June 2017, meaning thousands of more vulnerable Queenslanders will be forced to deal with their legal problems without any help.
We are calling on Attorney General and Attorney General George Brandis, as well as Queensland Senators, to end these funding cuts immediately so that people can get the help they need with legal problems.
Last year, the state government fulfilled its promise to increase legal aid funding to the national average.
